</taxonomicName>
’-LIKE SPECIES
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BE4E15A2A18F13DFF560FD64DDC6ADA" blockId="48.[142,640,732,754]" box="[142,640,732,754]" pageId="48" pageNumber="491">
<emphasis id="B92F3D482A18F13DFF560FD64E846AD9" box="[142,472,732,754]" italics="true" pageId="48" pageNumber="491">
New species from 
<collectingCountry id="F34CA1CA2A18F13DFE830FD74E846AD9" box="[347,472,732,754]" name="Costa Rica" pageId="48" pageNumber="491">Costa Rica</collectingCountry>
</emphasis>
: 
<emphasis id="B92F3D482A18F13DFE3E0FD64DDC6ADA" box="[486,640,732,754]" italics="true" pageId="48" pageNumber="491">
<taxonomicName id="4C5B9AD92A18F13DFE3E0FD64D206ADA" authorityName="Goldschmidt" authorityYear="2007" box="[486,636,732,754]" class="Arachnida" family="Torrenticolidae" genus="Torrenticola" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="48" pageNumber="491" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="flexirostris">T. flexirostris</taxonomicName>
.
</emphasis>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C341B2D12A18F13FFF560E014E516CFF" lastPageId="50" lastPageNumber="493" pageId="48" pageNumber="491" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="8BE4E15A2A18F13DFF560E014D9D6B92" blockId="48.[142,757,778,953]" pageId="48" pageNumber="491">
<emphasis id="B92F3D482A18F13DFF560E014D746B0B" box="[142,552,778,800]" italics="true" pageId="48" pageNumber="491">Differential diagnosis of the group</emphasis>
: Idiosoma oval; Cx-I/II broad, apically triangular with pointed tips; genital field large; capitulum basal relatively high, bend towards elongated, up-curved rostrum; palps without (with very small) ventral projections at P2 and P3; cheliceral claws straightened, elongated.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BE4E15A2A18F13DFF560ED94ED06D7C" blockId="48.[142,758,977,1367]" pageId="48" pageNumber="491">
<emphasis id="B92F3D482A18F13DFF560ED94E546BCC" box="[142,264,978,999]" italics="true" pageId="48" pageNumber="491">Discussion</emphasis>
: The ‘ 
<taxonomicName id="4C5B9AD92A18F13DFEB80EDA4EB86BCD" authorityName="Halbert" authorityYear="1944" box="[352,484,977,998]" class="Arachnida" family="Torrenticolidae" genus="Megapalpis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Acari" pageId="48" pageNumber="491" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B92F3D482A18F13DFEB80EDA4EB86BCD" box="[352,484,977,998]" italics="true" pageId="48" pageNumber="491">Megapalpis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
’-like species group is named after the subgenus 
<taxonomicName id="4C5B9AD92A18F13DFE110EFB4DAA6C2E" authority="Halbert, 1944" authorityName="Halbert" authorityYear="1944" box="[457,758,1008,1030]" class="Arachnida" family="Torrenticolidae" genus="Megapalpis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Acari" pageId="48" pageNumber="491" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B92F3D482A18F13DFE110EFB4D116C2E" box="[457,589,1008,1029]" italics="true" pageId="48" pageNumber="491">Megapalpis</emphasis>
Halbert, 1944
</taxonomicName>
until now only known from Europe and Asia (
<bibRefCitation id="EFCA9CAB2A18F13DFD4A09044E0E6C68" author="Di Sabatino A &amp; Gerecke R &amp; Smit H &amp; Pesic V &amp; Panesar A" pageId="48" pageNumber="491" pagination="393 - 431" refId="ref112191" refString="Di Sabatino A, Gerecke R, Smit H, Pesic V, Panesar A. 2003 b. Water mites of the family Torrenticolidae (Acari, Actinedida, Hydrachnidia) from the Eastern Mediterranean. Archiv fur Hydrobiologie Supplement 139: 393 - 431." type="journal article" year="2003">
Di Sabatino 
<emphasis id="B92F3D482A18F13DFF1C09254FA86C69" box="[196,244,1069,1091]" italics="true" pageId="48" pageNumber="491">et al</emphasis>
., 2003b
</bibRefCitation>
). At the present state of knowledge, with only one species of this group known from Central America, it cannot be decided if this species group could be regarded as a phylogenetic entity. Besides some striking similarities between the new species from 
<collectingCountry id="F34CA1CA2A18F13DFF1109CC4E1D6CF6" box="[201,321,1223,1245]" name="Costa Rica" pageId="48" pageNumber="491">Costa Rica</collectingCountry>
and the species of the subgenus 
<taxonomicName id="4C5B9AD92A18F13DFD6809CC4F886CD1" authorityName="Halbert" authorityYear="1944" class="Arachnida" family="Torrenticolidae" genus="Megapalpis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Acari" pageId="48" pageNumber="491" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B92F3D482A18F13DFD6809CC4F886CD1" italics="true" pageId="48" pageNumber="491">Megapalpis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from the Old World, there are also some differences (see below). Therefore, at the present state of knowledge, the new species should not be placed within that subgenus.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BE4E15A2A18F13DFF0F08994DF16D81" blockId="48.[215,685,1426,1482]" box="[215,685,1426,1450]" pageId="48" pageNumber="491">
