<paragraph id="8BE4E15A2A1AF13FFF560E654E516CFF" blockId="50.[142,758,877,1236]" pageId="50" pageNumber="493">
<emphasis id="B92F3D482A1AF13FFF560E654E546BA8" box="[142,264,878,899]" italics="true" pageId="50" pageNumber="493">Discussion</emphasis>
: 
<taxonomicName id="4C5B9AD92A1AF13FFEF20E664D146BA9" authorityName="Goldschmidt" authorityYear="2007" box="[298,584,877,898]" class="Arachnida" family="Torrenticolidae" genus="Torrenticola" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="50" pageNumber="493" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="flexirostris">
<emphasis id="B92F3D482A1AF13FFEF20E664D146BA9" box="[298,584,877,898]" italics="true" pageId="50" pageNumber="493">Torrenticola flexirostris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from 
<collectingCountry id="F34CA1CA2A1AF13FFD6D0E664F9C6B89" name="Costa Rica" pageId="50" pageNumber="493">Costa Rica</collectingCountry>
differs from the European and Asian species of the subgenus 
<taxonomicName id="4C5B9AD92A1AF13FFE860EA14EBE6B94" authorityName="Halbert" authorityYear="1944" box="[350,482,938,959]" class="Arachnida" family="Torrenticolidae" genus="Megapalpis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Acari" pageId="50" pageNumber="493" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B92F3D482A1AF13FFE860EA14EBE6B94" box="[350,482,938,959]" italics="true" pageId="50" pageNumber="493">Megapalpis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in the clearly shorter palps and rostrum, and therefore it should not be assigned to this subgenus. However, the characteristic shape of the rostrum, cheliceral claw and Cx- I/II, as well as – to a certain extent – of the palps, strongly suggests the classification of 
<taxonomicName id="4C5B9AD92A1AF13FFF5609684E7D6C5C" authorityName="Goldschmidt" authorityYear="2007" box="[142,289,1122,1144]" class="Arachnida" family="Torrenticolidae" genus="Torrenticola" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="50" pageNumber="493" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="flexirostris">
<emphasis id="B92F3D482A1AF13FFF5609684E7D6C5C" box="[142,289,1122,1144]" italics="true" pageId="50" pageNumber="493">T. flexirostris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in a separate group. The new species differs from all other species known from Central and South America in this combination of characters.
</paragraph>
